<subSubSection id="6DE16501251CFF9DFF451205FC89FC23" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF451205FC89FC23" blockId="9.[178,1085,855,908]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) is derived from the name of the mountain (Kurama-yama) where the species was discovered.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DE16501251CFF9FFF4512C9FCE3FD72" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1626" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624" type="description">
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF4512C9FC92FC43" blockId="9.[178,1085,923,1004]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">
Description: Species of moderately large size; body length 
<quantity id="E2039B6F251CFF9DFC8812CEFC40FC1E" box="[895,978,924,945]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624" unit="mm" value="7.7">7.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="E2039B6F251CFF9DFEE212EBFEF5FC61" box="[277,359,953,975]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFDF512EBFDDCFC60" box="[514,590,953,975]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head blackish-brown; remainder of body castaneous; legs yellowish-brown; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF4512A9FCDCFB29" blockId="9.[178,1086,1019,1158]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">
Head (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFF0112A9FED2FBBE" box="[246,320,1019,1041]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) rather large in relation to remainder of body, 1.05 times as broad as long, not distinctly dilated posteriad; punctation moderately coarse and moderately dense, sparser in median dorsal portion; interstices with fine and shallow microreticulation. Eyes approximately one fourth as long as postocular region in dorsal view, flat, and composed of approximately 50 ommatidia. Antenna 
<quantity id="E2039B6F251CFF9DFD301522FC86FB29" box="[711,788,1136,1158]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF4515C4FDECFB49" blockId="9.[178,1085,1174,1254]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFED315C4FEFCFB03" box="[292,366,1174,1196]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 1.15 times as long as broad and 0.98 times as broad as head; anterior three fourths of lateral margins subparallel in dorsal view; punctation similar to that of head; impunctate median band rather narrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF4515A7FDC7FAE9" blockId="9.[178,1085,1269,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFF0915A7FEDAFAA4" box="[254,328,1269,1291]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 0.56 times as long as pronotum, very weakly dilated posteriad; combined posterior margins very weakly concave; punctation rather fine, shallow, and weakly defined. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9DFF451407FC0AFA09" blockId="9.[178,1085,1365,1446]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Abdomen 1.1 times as broad as elytra; punctation fine and dense, nearly as dense on tergite VII as on anterior tergites; interstices with fine and very shallow microsculpture, somewhat glossy; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251CFF9EFF3014E4FE8EFE2C" blockId="9.[178,1085,1461,1600]" lastBlockId="10.[178,1086,218,387]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="1625" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">
: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; tergite VIII with very weakly convex posterior margin; tergite IX elongated and slender, much longer than broad; sternites III-VI unmodified; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFE5514A2FE7FF9A9" box="[418,493,1520,1542]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse and with shallow postero-median impression, this impression with sparse pubescence, pubescence not distinctly modified; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251CFF9DFEB51778FE02F9EF" box="[322,400,1578,1600]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1624">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad, posteriorly somewhat produced and with posterior excision of nearly semi-circular shape; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F251FFF9EFC871188FC73FF5F" box="[880,993,218,240]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" captionTargetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[178,1085,438,1516]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 17-22: Lathrobium kuramaicum nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VII; (20) male sternite VIII; (21-22) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">
Figs 21 
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFC491188FC54FF5F" bold="true" box="[958,966,218,240]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">-</emphasis>
22
</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="E2039B6F251FFF9EFC181188FBAFFF5F" box="[1007,1085,218,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
long and somewhat asymmetric; ventral process conspicuously elongated, very slender and apically acute, weakly curved in lateral view, and slightly asymmetric in ventral view; dorsal plate with conspicuously long, distinctly asymmetric, and apically convex apical portion, and with very short curved basal portion; internal sac without sclerotized structures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251FFF9FFF3010C1FDA4FEC9" blockId="10.[199,314,402,424]" lastBlockId="11.[178,1085,218,358]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1626" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">
: unknown. Comparative notes: The similarly derived male sexual characters suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFF1411ABFE12FEA1" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[227,384,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuramaicum">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFF1411ABFE12FEA1" box="[227,384,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kuramaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFDAD11ABFC3AFEA1" authority="WATANABE 2011" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2011" box="[602,936,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masumotoi">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFDAD11ABFD7AFEA1" box="[602,744,249,270]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. masumotoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B251EFF9FFD0411AAFC3AFEA1" author="WATANABE Y" box="[755,936,248,270]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" pagination="103 - 108" refId="ref11868" refString="WATANABE Y. (2011): Two new species of the brachypterous Lathrobium (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from the Northern Japanese Alps in Central Honshu, Japan. - Special Publication of the Japanese Society of Scarabaeoidology, Tokyo 1: 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="2011">WATANABE 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251EFF9FFC1911AAFE88FE84" country="Japan" name="Nagano" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">Nagano Prefecture</collectingRegion>
(Central Honshu) and 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFDFF1044FC2FFE84" authority="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA 2003" authorityName="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA" authorityYear="2003" box="[520,957,277,299]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagaense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFDFF1044FD11FE84" box="[520,643,277,299]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kagaense</emphasis>
WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA 2003
</taxonomicName>
from Hakusan, a mountain in southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251EFF9FFE081060FD58FEE7" box="[511,714,306,328]" country="Japan" name="Ishikawa" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">Ishikawa Prefecture</collectingRegion>
(Central Honshu). The new species is distinguished from them as follows:
</paragraph>
<caption id="71846602251FFF9EFF4514A4FEADF997" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303079" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5303079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303079/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625" startId="10.[178,218,1526,1546]" targetBox="[188,1059,438,1509]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="2544368A251FFF9EFF4514A4FEADF997" blockId="10.[178,1086,1526,1592]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFF4514A4FE85F9A5" bold="true" box="[178,279,1526,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">Figs 17-22</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251FFF9EFED214A4FD9BF9A5" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[293,521,1526,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuramaicum" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFED214A4FD9BF9A5" box="[293,521,1526,1546]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">Lathrobium kuramaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0CBC57E3251FFF9EFDE614A4FDC5F9A5" box="[529,599,1526,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFD9F14A4FDEDF9A5" bold="true" box="[616,639,1526,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">17</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFD1214A4FD6EF9A5" bold="true" box="[741,764,1526,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">18</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFC8414A4FC18F9A5" bold="true" box="[883,906,1526,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">19</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFF4D175FFF43F98E" bold="true" box="[186,209,1549,1569]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">20</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="178FEA98251FFF9EFE62175FFE58F98E" bold="true" box="[405,458,1549,1569]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1625">21-22</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2544368A251EFF9FFF451027FD48FDB2" blockId="11.[178,1085,373,541]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">
from 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFF1C1024FEE4FE24" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2011" box="[235,374,374,395]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masumotoi">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFF1C1024FEE4FE24" box="[235,374,374,395]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. masumotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the relatively larger head, the denser punctation of the pronotum, the posteriorly less distinctly dilated elytra, the less distinctly concave combined posterior margins of the elytra, the much narrower posterior excision of the male sternite VIII, and the morphology of the smaller aedeagus (
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFD70109CFC80FE4C" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2011" box="[647,786,462,483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masumotoi">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFD70109CFC80FE4C" box="[647,786,462,483]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. masumotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: length of aedeagus 
<quantity id="E2039B6F251EFF9FFC1F109FFBABFE4D" box="[1000,1081,461,483]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
; ventral process strongly laterally compressed, somewhat twisted, and more strongly curved in lateral view; dorsal plate of different shape).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251EFF9FFF45137EFDECFD35" blockId="11.[178,1085,556,666]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">
from 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFF19137FFEF9FDED" authorityName="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA" authorityYear="2003" box="[238,363,556,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagaense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFF19137FFEF9FDED" box="[238,363,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kagaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the unmodified male sternite VI (
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFCF2137FFC10FDED" authorityName="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA" authorityYear="2003" box="[773,898,556,578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagaense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFCF2137FFC10FDED" box="[773,898,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kagaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: sternite VI with oblong impression in the middle), the deeper posterior excision of the male sternite VIII, and by the shape of the aedeagus (
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFDD6133AFD0FFDD2" authorityName="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA" authorityYear="2003" box="[545,669,615,637]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagaense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFDD6133AFD0FFDD2" box="[545,669,615,637]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kagaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: ventral process less slender and somewhat twisted; dorsal plate of different shape).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A251EFF9FFF4513F8FCE3FD72" blockId="11.[178,1085,682,733]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">
For illustrations of the male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFD3E13F9FCCAFD6F" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2011" box="[713,856,683,704]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masumotoi">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFD3E13F9FCCAFD6F" box="[713,856,683,704]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. masumotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251EFF9FFC6413F9FB83FD6F" authorityName="WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA" authorityYear="2003" box="[915,1041,682,704]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagaense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251EFF9FFC6413F9FB83FD6F" box="[915,1041,682,704]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">L. kagaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B251EFF9FFF45139AFEE1FD72" author="WATANABE Y" box="[178,371,711,733]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" pagination="103 - 108" refId="ref11868" refString="WATANABE Y. (2011): Two new species of the brachypterous Lathrobium (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from the Northern Japanese Alps in Central Honshu, Japan. - Special Publication of the Japanese Society of Scarabaeoidology, Tokyo 1: 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="2011">WATANABE (2011)</bibRefCitation>
and WATANABE &amp; HOSHINA (2003), respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DE16501251EFF9FFF4513BEFC56FCB0" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2544368A251EFF9FFF4513BEFC56FCB0" blockId="11.[178,1085,748,799]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">
Distribution: The 
<typeStatus id="FA408828251EFF9FFE2A13BFFD9BFCAD" box="[477,521,749,770]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated on the Kurama-yama (
<geoCoordinate id="40CF504D251EFF9FFC1513BEFBABFCAD" box="[994,1081,748,770]" degrees="35" direction="north" minutes="07" orientation="latitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" precision="925" value="35.116665">35°07'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="40CF504D251EFF9FFF45125BFE81FCB0" box="[178,275,777,799]" degrees="130" direction="east" minutes="35" orientation="longitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626" precision="925" value="130.58333">130°35'E</geoCoordinate>
), a mountain in Kyoto-fu, to the north of 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251EFF9FFD401258FD6BFCB0" box="[695,761,778,799]" country="Japan" name="Kyoto" pageId="11" pageNumber="1626">Kyoto</collectingRegion>
, in Central Honshu.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
